definition: gate/door/CL:扇[shan4]/gateway/doorway/CL:個|个[ge4]/opening/valve/switch/way to do something/knack/family/house/(religious) sect/school (of thought)/class/category/phylum or division (taxonomy)/classifier for large guns/classifier for lessons, subjects, branches of technology/(suffix) -gate (i.e. scandal; derived from Watergate)

sentences.english: A handsome grilled gateway opens to the garden of all desired things.
sentences.chinese: 通向渴望之園的那扇富麗堂皇的格柵門大敞開着。

sentences.english: Introduced the injection mold structure of the plastic products of the air chute fence gate.
sentences.chinese: 介紹了通風道柵門塑料產品的注射模結構。

sentences.english: What prints did you see by the moor gate?
sentences.chinese: 你在柵門處看到了什麼痕跡？

sentences.english: We walked through the gate of the picket fence and proceeded to look around.
sentences.chinese: 我們走過尖樁籬柵門，四處觀望。

sentences.english: She reached a turnpike-gate which stood upon the highway to the village.
sentences.chinese: 她走到了通向村子的那條大道的收稅柵門。

sentences.english: After he passed the gate, only toe prints could be seen.
sentences.chinese: 但過了柵門之後，則只能看到他腳趾的印記了。

sentences.english: Help a lame dog over a stile.
sentences.chinese: 幫助跛足的狗越過柵門。

sentences.english: He jumped over the gate into the field.
Were they on the same side of the path as the moor gate?
sentences.chinese: 是在與開向沼地的柵門同一路邊上嗎？

sentences.english: The sheepdog rounded up the sheep and drove them through the gate.
sentences.chinese: 牧羊犬把羊攆到了一起，把它們趕過柵門。

sentences.english: I heard a voice at the turnstile I had not heard for many years.
sentences.chinese: 我聽到在旋轉柵門那兒有一個多年沒有聽到的嗓聲。
